<TITLE> Leaders issue Eid messages for peace </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 27 (bdnews24.com)President Zillur Rahman, prime minister Sheikh Hasina and opposition chief Khaleda Zia issued messages of peace and prosperity as Muslims in Bangladesh prepared for Eid-ul-Azha. "We have to reflect the great lesson of the sacrifice of Eid-ul-Azha in our thought and work to build a peaceful and tolerant society," the president said in his message ahead of the holiday. "I believe Eidul-Azha will further strengthen the unity, solidarity and brotherhood of the Muslim nation," he said. The prime minister called on all to participate in the people's welfare activities from their respective position to build a disparity-free, happy and rich Bangladesh imbued with the spirit of Eid-ul-Azha. "The unique instance which Hazrat Ibrahim (A) established through the sacrifice of his dear one for Allah will remain forever as one to follow for the world," said Hasina. Opposition leader Khaleda Zia said, "The prime lesson of Eid-Ul-Azha is to sacrifice self interest and dedicate oneself to the welfare of the humanity." "Our duty is to get engaged in establishing peace and harmony in society by avoiding envy, spite, greed and anger." The opposition leader asked the well-off section in society to help the poor and hapless. bdnew
